    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried looking at my schedule but it's kind of hard to follow. it feels like there are these hidden little things eating away at my progress. like, even when i pay extra, the balance just seems to stall out. is there any specific math term for when these extra costs or interest accruals basically work against you and slow down the whole process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "What you're experiencing is due to \"specific rateposts\" or \"specific prorations\", but more commonly known as \"computed interest\" or \"outstanding balance interest\". It's a calculation where your loan earns interest on your original loan amount, meaning it's a compound interest effect. Essentially, the interest is being added before the extra payment or part of the payment is applied to the principal, resulting in it not immediately reducing the overall balance.",
      "source": "target",
